In a JSP page, the page object (see below) in the generated servlet code is typed as Object instead of HttpJspPage, which makes it difficult to call meaningful methods on it.

    PageContext pageContext = null;
    ServletContext application = null;
    ServletConfig config = null;
    JspWriter out = null;
    Object page = this;
    JspWriter _jspx_out = null;
    PageContext _jspx_page_context = null;

The workaround is to use "this" instead.
